2 (c) Establishing a procedure that allows for a timely appeal of decisions to the
3 school-based decision making council and ultimately to the local school
4 board.
5 (11) An expression made by a student journalist in the exercise of free speech or free
6 press rights under this section shall not be deemed to be an expression of school
7 policy, and a school official or school district shall not be held responsible in any
8 civil or criminal action for any expression made or published by a student
9 journalist.
10 (12) Any student journalist, individually or through a parent or guardian, or student
11 media advisor may institute proceedings for injunctive or declaratory relief in any
12 court of competent jurisdiction to enforce the rights provided in this section.
13 Nothing in this section shall be construed to create any private action on behalf
14 of a student other than to seek injunctive relief allowing the publication of the
15 school-sponsored media in question. A court may award reasonable attorney's
16 fees to a plaintiff that substantially prevails.
17 Section 2. This Act may be cited as the New Voices Act.
